  "original_title": "\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bbf \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Farmer killed in elephant attack",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "A farmer who was on field guard was killed yesterday evening (09) after being attacked by a wild elephant in Kandiyanaru village of Vaunadivu police division of Batticaloa district, the police said.",
        "Karunakaran (57 years old), a father of four from Unnichai area, was killed in the accident.",
        "On the day of the incident, while he was tending to his violin in Kandianar area from his home, a wild elephant suddenly entered the violin and attacked the person.",
        "During the initial investigation of the police, it was revealed that the farmer who was guarding the field in Ayal, who was seriously injured, died after being taken to the Thandiyadi hospital.",
        "According to the order of the Batticaloa court judge, Vaunadivu District Sudden Death Investigation Officer Thampipillai Tavakumar, who went to Samba, visited the body and ordered the police to hand over the body to the relatives after the post-mortem."
      ],
